This paper deals with cooperative transmission in vehicular networks, which involves the use of communication technologies and network protocols. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also uses coalitional game theory to analyze the behaviors of the vehicles and RSUs, which suggests the possibility of cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as a likely category. The paper also discusses the pricing mechanism, which is related to cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also considers the mobility of the vehicles, which suggests the possibility of cs.SY (Systems and Control) as a likely category. Finally, the paper presents numerical results, which suggests the possibility of cs.MM (Multimedia) as a likely category.
